  <front>
   <head>Written for my Son, to Mr. Barry; occasion'd by the foregoing Verses.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">makes your Verse divine,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Since the God glows in ev'ry Line;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Why should you think, but I, with Ease,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Might write my native, artless Lays?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Mother told me many a Time,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">That Double-dealing was a Crime:</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Alas! and is it only so,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In us, whose Birth and Fortune's low?</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For you, tho' nobly born, descend</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To injure, yet appear a Friend;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And seem to make my Praise your Aim,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With more Success to wound my Fame.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">your  Priests, of old,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">(As by his Poets we are told)</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With glorious Wreaths the Victim drest;</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Then plung'd the Poniard in his Breast.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
